This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and semi-supervised learning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), respectively. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper uses the Transformer model, which is a neural network architecture commonly used in NLP and ML. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of image-based techniques for data augmentation, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
